This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to identify products being bought and sold in online cybercrime forums. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and information retrieval. The paper also deals with cybercrime, which suggests the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of machine learning techniques suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the study of domain adaptation suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
